text: Ana Carolina Cosse Garrido (born 25 December 1961) is a Uruguayan engineer and politician who has been the 19th and current vice president of Uruguay since 2025. She and ticket leader Yamandú Orsi won the 2024 general election. She was the Intendant of Montevideo from 2020 until 2024. She is a member of the Broad Front. She was the Minister of Industry, Energy, and Mining from 2015 to 2019 during the second administration of President Tabaré Vázquez. In the 2019 Uruguayan general election, she was elected to the Senate of Uruguay. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Living people Category:1962 births Category:Politicians from Montevideo Category:Vice presidents of Uruguay
